|title=[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/9379477.stm Arsenal 2-1 Everton]
|passage=Everton took that disputed lead in a moment that caused anger to sweep around the Emirates.}}
# {{lb|en|cricket}} To play a sweep shot.
# {{lb|en|curling}} To [[brush]] the [[ice]] in front of a moving [[stone]], causing it to travel farther and to [[curl]] less.
# {{lb|en|transitive|ergative}} To move something in a particular motion, as a [[broom]].
# {{lb|en|sports|transitive}} To [[win]] (a [[series]]) without [[draw]]ing or [[lose|losing]] any of the games in that series.
# {{lb|en|sports|transitive}} To [[defeat]] (a team) in a [[series]] without [[draw]]ing or [[lose|losing]] any of the games in that series.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[remove]] something [[abruptly]] and [[thoroughly]].
#: {{ux|en|She '''swept''' the peelings off the table onto the floor.}}
#: ''The wind '''sweeps''' the snow from the hills.''
#: ''The flooded river '''swept''' away the wooden dam.''
